# --- Version-specific noSig entries surfaced by full-CI (act) closure ---
#
# These artifacts have no .asc signature on Maven Central at the specific
# version+packaging listed. They were surfaced when pgpverify ran against
# a fresh ~/.m2 (matching real CI behavior) and saw a larger transitive
# plugin closure than the dev-container bootstrap captured.
#
# noSig at the version:packaging level is more precise than at the
# groupId:artifactId level — it lets future versions (which may add
# signatures) be re-evaluated rather than blanket-trusted.
#
# Generated from test-logs/local-act-verifypgp.log via:
#   grep -oE "Unsigned artifact .* in keys map: [^[:space:]]+" \
#     test-logs/local-act-verifypgp.log | sed -E 's/^.*: //' | sort -u
#
